@node wit "What Is Move2.0"

  What Is This
   ----------

 Move is a CLI-Command that copies a file somewhere other and deletes the
 source. It just moves files like all the other movers do. But wait, some-
 thing is different: Move also moves the icon of the file if some exists!
 I can`t find any mover doing this, exept DOpus of course.
@endnode
@node hti "How To Install Move2.0"

  How To Install
   ------------

 The answer is easy: Just copy Move2.0 to your C directory!
@endnode
@node htu "How To Use Move2.0"

  How To Use
   --------

 Give the source and the target after the command like this:

  Move2.0 drive0:dir0/file drive1:dir1/dir2

 And you can also give the argument help after the command and a text how
 to use Move2.0 will be displayed:

  Move2.0 help
@endnode
